Gemini CLI Termux is a porting/distribution fork of Google's Gemini CLI for
Android ARM64 (Termux). It carries only the Android/Termux compatibility
delta needed to package and run upstream Gemini CLI on Termux (PTY support
via @mmmbuto/pty-termux-utils, termux-open-url integration for auth/browser
flows, optional tts_notification backed by termux-tts-speak, Termux
environment detection). These compatibility patches are maintained by
Davide A. Guglielmi and distributed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
together with the upstream Gemini CLI codebase.

Upstream project: https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli
